# Coolify API Token Configuration
#
# Create an API token via Coolify UI:
# 1. Access Coolify: http://192.168.0.160:8000
# 2. Log in with admin credentials
# 3. Navigate to: Settings → Security → API Tokens
# 4. Click "Create New Token"
#    - Name: ansible-automation
#    - Permissions: Uncheck "Read Only" for full (*) access
# 5. Copy the token (shown only once!)
# 6. Paste below

COOLIFY_API_TOKEN=your_token_here

# GitHub App Configuration (Optional - for repository deployments)
#
# One-time setup to create a GitHub App:
# 1. Go to: https://github.com/settings/apps/new
# 2. Fill in:
#    - GitHub App name: coolify-homelab
#    - Homepage URL: http://192.168.0.160:8000
#    - Webhook URL: http://192.168.0.160:8000/webhooks/github
#    - Webhook secret: Generate random string (save for below)
#    - Permissions:
#      * Repository permissions:
#        - Contents: Read & write
#        - Metadata: Read-only
#        - Pull requests: Read & write
#        - Webhooks: Read & write
#      * Subscribe to events: Push, Pull request
# 3. Click "Create GitHub App"
# 4. Generate private key (Download the .pem file)
# 5. Install app to your organization/repositories
# 6. Copy all values below:

GITHUB_APP_ID=
GITHUB_INSTALLATION_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=
GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY=
